TYPE CONVERSION IN PYTHON:
• Type conversion means changing the data type of a value.

In Python, there are two types of type conversion:
ⅰ) Implicit Conversion
ⅱ) Explicit Conversion 

ⅰ) Implicit Conversion:
Python automatically converts one data type to another during operations without user intervention.

→ Example:
a = 5     # int
b = 2.5   # float
result = a + b       # a is automatically converted to float
print(result)        # 7.5
print(type(result))  # <class 'float'>

ⅱ) Explicit Conversion:
The programmer manually converts the data type using built-in functions.

⇒ Common Type Casting Functions:
Function	                      Converts To
int()	                          Integer
float()	                        Floating point
str()	                          String
bool()	                        Boolean
list()	                        List
tuple()	                        Tuple
set()	                          Set
complex()	                      Complex number

→ Examples:
➤ Convert float to int:
x = 9.7
y = int(x)
print(y)  # 9

➤ Convert string to int:
s = "123"
n = int(s)
print(n + 1)  # 124
